Brazil May Raise Currency Futures Tax to Stem Real’s Increase, Valor Says

-- B y   F r a n c i s c o   M a r c e l i n o
-- 
2011-07-13T11:13:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-13/brazil-may-raise-tax-on-currency-future-contracts-to-stem-real-valor-says.html
Brazil ’s government is considering
raising a tax on currency future contracts to contain the
appreciation of the real against the U.S. dollar, Valor
Economico reported, without saying where it got the information.  Among other options, the government is studying increasing
taxes on margin guarantees deposited by foreign investors at
 BM&FBovespa SA (BVMF3)  when trading future currency contracts, the Sao
Paulo-based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Francisco Marcelino in Sao Paulo at 
 mdeoliveira@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
